Bertoxx <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usharafi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sharafi</A> at: 3/10/02 9:32:23 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uravden.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ravden</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/11/02 2:04:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22695.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> Clerics can get extremely boring. The only time I have fun on my cleric is hard groups. Sitting in a camp in say seb chardok HS velks etc. gets too boring and trivial. Doing stuff like crawling way back in DN and doing the 60 nameds are fun and intense. In a normal exp group of pull Cheal sit etc. Usualy in those groups im almost always FM so I nuke my ass off, this makes it more fun but still pretty boring. I'd chose rogue clerics will always be needed, but there will always be clerics there. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ustevostevo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stevostevo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/11/02 4:49:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22695.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> Just to continue with the negative points made by Daese TYoo...<br>
<br>
A major difference between a rogue and a cleric is that you are just not essential for anything, so its kind of hard to be really useful or helpful.<br>
<br>
After raids, there is always somebody in my guild who needs help with something or other for a quest.  One or two man kills or whatever.  I like to help, but I am very rarely any use, unless a whole group has already been formed, in which case, they would be able to do what they need to do without me if they wanted.<br>
<br>
Its harder to form groups as you are not an essential part of a group - you are not a tank, healer, crowd control or porter / evac.  You only have a useful function once the core of the group is already in place.<br>
<br>
Minor points, sure, but maybe a culture shock from being a cleric where you are more important - groups break up when the cleric logs etc.<br>
<br>
Stevo <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#FF0000>- </font><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse>The Safehouse</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion>Main Lounge</a> <font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href="http://www.thesafehouse.org">The Safehouse website</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font> <center><a href="http://www.guildboss.com"><img
